<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Soak tamarind in boiling water for half an hour or so]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Make curry paste by putting all ingredients one by one in mortar, or food processor]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Deep fry the tofu, drain on paper towels]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[If you are cooking rice, steam the eggs over it. Otherwise just hard boil normally.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Reduce coconut cream, 5 or 6 mins stirring regularly, then add 3 tbsp curry paste, 7 mins or so.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the palm sugar, a few minutes until darkened, and the sieved tamarind water and fish sauce / fermented beans, a few more minutes]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[In another pan mix a bit of the coconut milk with the oil. When hot fry the peppers in it for 5 mins or so.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Pour the peppers and reduced coconut milk into the cream sauce with the peas, tofu, kaffir lime leaves, and soya sauce. Cook 10 minutes until done.]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
